    "analysis": "The previous Executor run computed global aggregates (count, min/max timestamp, global P95/P5) for metric, trace, and log groups and returned error_log samples. Key findings from that step: IG01 has very large JVM HeapMemoryUsed (global P95 ~8.45e8) and other JVM metrics; IG01 and IG02 trace.self.duration_p95 reach the ceiling 60.0s (suggesting long/blocked traces); Tomcat02 shows elevated log.error_count (global P95 = 4) and 18 raw error log entries concentrated between 2021-03-06 18:30:45 and 18:35:35 CST. From these aggregates we have three strong candidates to investigate further: IG01 (JVM/trace slow/high heap), IG02 (trace high p95), and Tomcat02 (error spikes). Next we must follow the prescribed order: threshold calculation (already available), then filter data to the failure window and run metric anomaly detection to narrow down which component-KPI series show consecutive anomalies during 2021-03-06 18:30:00 to 2021-03-06 19:00:00 (UTC+8).",
